ABUJA – Nigeria and the Republic of India have pledged to work more closely to enhance energy security of both countries. Ndu Ughamadu, Group General Manager, Group Public Affairs, Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC), said in a statement that the consensus came on the heels of the Indian High Commissioner to Nigeria, Abhay Thakur’s, visit to the Group Managing Director, NNPC, Dr. Maikanti Baru, on Tuesday in Abuja. The statement noted that Dr. Baru acknowledged the role of Indian companies in Nigeria, and called on them to extend their presence to the downstream sector of the petroleum industry to leverage on the enormous opportunities there. He assured the Indian high commissioner of NNPC’s commitment to further strengthening the existing relations between both countries in the energy sector. The GMD noted that with the refineries up for repairs, the corporation would need technical assistance from Indian companies.